It&#8217;s understood officers approached him while he was in the company of his girlfriend and he opened fire. JOHANNESBURG - Soweto police have shot and killed a man in Dobsonville.It s understood officers approached the man last night while he was in the company of his girlfriend and he opened fire.The suspect was wounded and later died in hospital.Police spokesperson Kay Makhubela says police have opened cases of attempted murder. They approached him, he started shooting at the police and he was standing with his girlfriend. He was shot and later he died at the hospital. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)